-----------
Libraries needed
-----------
You will need the following libraries to compile the sources:
* libz
* Boost (for the BOOST_FOREACH() macro)

-----------------
Building the source
-----------------
There are two ways to build the source. With cmake or with autotools. I personally use cmake.

-----------------
Building using cmake
-----------------
Go into the 'build' directory.
Issue 'cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo ../'
Issue 'make'
Type in './cryptominisat satfile' to test your new code.

------------------
Building using autotools
------------------
Verify that the symlink 'ltmain.sh' is not broken
Issue 'automake --add-missing'
Issue 'make -f Makefile.cvs'
Go to the 'build' directory
Issue 'CXXFLAGS="-O3 -g" ../configure'
Type 'make'
Type in './cryptominisat satfile' to test your new code.

---------
Please read help
---------
For help, build the program, and issue:
'./minisat -help'

--------
Verbose debug
--------
You can also turn on verbose debugging.
Simply add "#define VERBOSE_DEBUG" to the Solver/Solver.h file and re-compile

When executing:
'./minisat satfile'
You will see a LOT of debug info. You should therefore maybe do:
'./minisat satfile > debuginfo.txt'
then you can open the 'debuginfo.txt' file from a text editor and have a look

---------
Users looking for better performance
--------
If using configure: Use 'CXXFLAGS="-O3 -g0 -march=native"'

If using cmake, replace the line in CMakeLists.txt:
'set(CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS="-g -Wall -O3 -Wno-deprecated")'
with
'set(CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS="-g0 -Wall -O3 -march=native -Wno-deprecated")'

-----------------
Windows use
----------------
With cmake it should be relatively simple.

I compile under linux all windows binaries, using gcc that generates windows executables. It works really well. There is a sort-of-howto in the src/Solver/win32-howto text file. A short step-by-step is here: 

1) Install gcc that generates windows binaries:

i586-mingw32msvc

1) Install all libraries (BOOST, libz) 

BOOST:
http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=204414

libz:
get from source and compile as per src/Solver/win32-howto

2) complie:

go to "src/Solver" and do:

i586-mingw32msvc-g++ -O3 -g0 -DCROSS_COMPILE  -march=i586 -I../mtl/ -I../MTRand/ Main.C /usr/i586-mingw32msvc/lib/libz.a Solver.C Logger.C fcopy.cpp clause.cpp -o minisat.exe

I test the generated binary under wine, in Linux.
